HEADWORD: Lowbred
<hw>Low"bred`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Bred, or like one
bred, in a low condition of life; characteristic or indicative of such
breeding; rude; impolite; vulgar; <as>as, a <ex>lowbred</ex> fellow; a
<ex>lowbred</ex> remark.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>low-cal</ent>⟦br⟧
